{
  "name": "RPlog_That_Damned_Stupidly_Heroic_Corellian",
  "title": "The Stab Wound and the Jedi's Hand",
  "summary": "On sun-baked Palanhi, Jessalyn collects the scholar Paul Nighman from the Grand Palanhi Hotel and escorts him through the city to the starport where Shenner waits beside the freighter Black Dragon. As they prepare to leave, the menacing bounty hunter Vermillion -- whom a terrified Jessalyn recognizes -- stalks them off his ship and forces a confrontation, driving concealed forearm blades deep into Paul's side before Paul drives him off with a blaster shot. Bleeding heavily and slipping toward shock, Paul is hauled aboard and tended by Jessalyn and Shenner in the crew's quarters, where the women bandage his wounds while he frets over his luggage and slides in and out of lucidity. Luke Skywalker arrives and twice channels the Force, first easing Paul's pain and then partially closing the stab wounds, prompting Paul's wary musings about why a stranger would help him. With the danger past, the crew settles to rest, and Shenner finally sings the wounded Corellian into a healing sleep.",
